{{Quote|Your fate is clouded...but the will of the force has set your path. The man you seek you'll find inside; the one who needs you, you'll find in time. Fear not, for the "son of the suns" will free us all. Take care for the Bogan is heavy upon this system. May the FORCE OF OTHERS be with you.|Seer|<ref name="Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars">''[[Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars]]''</ref>}}
The '''Seer''' was an old, gray robed, man [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Starkiller]] encountered in [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], on [[Utapau/Legends|Utapau]]. He sat in front of the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Mos Eisley Cantina]] and assured the puzzled Luke that he would find the help he sought getting to [[Ogana Major]], and that the "[[Son of Suns/Legends|Son of the Suns]]" would free everyone.

The Seer partially spoke in rhythmic couplets.

==Behind the scenes==
*"Seer" is the only name this character was given in the script.

*This random old man becomes, in the [[Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars|story synopsis]] which was written between the second and third drafts, a more fleshed out character, an old [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and trainer of Luke's. In the third draft, he was combined with [[Kane Starkiller|The Starkiller]] to become [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Ben Kenobi]].

